Perfect — you have both, and rx_samples_to_file is the better one to use here.

Its CLI supports --file, --type {double,float,short}, --nsamps, --duration, --rate, --freq, --gain, --ant, and --otw. In the UHD example source, the defaults are --file usrp_samples.dat, --type short, --nsamps 0, and --duration 0, where 0 means continuous receive/write.  ￼

Do this

On the host, make a FIFO

rm -f /tmp/e320_iq.pipe
mkfifo /tmp/e320_iq.pipe

On the host, start the SSH stream from the E320 into the FIFO

Use the E320’s local UHD path and write to stdout:

ssh root@192.168.10.2 '/usr/lib/uhd/examples/rx_samples_to_file \
  --args "addr=127.0.0.1" \
  --file /dev/stdout \
  --type short \
  --rate 250000 \
  --freq 100000000 \
  --gain 20 \
  --nsamps 0' > /tmp/e320_iq.pipe

That uses interleaved IQ as 16-bit integers (short), which is easy to ingest on the host. The example source documents short as interleaved IQ in sc16-style integer form.  ￼

